On Thu, 15 Nov 2001, Chris Mills wrote:

> Please when you get a chance - I would love to see the info!
>
> I'm thinking stainless steel casings around OEM heat sinks and pipes
> (properly coated with a paint to slow any rusting) and this would eliminate
> any chance of exhaust fumes in the interior. When the OEM pipes and sinks
> rust out (but shouldn't be fast with a proper anitfreeze) you just dig out
> another set of rusted heater boxes, cut off the shell, move the watercooled
> shells from your old pipes to your "new" pipes.
>
> Should be several years per set or more.
>
> But how to pump the water around without a bunch of pulleys....

ONe of my students showed me an electric water pump in a Summit Racing
catalog.  Pumps something like 30gal/min, which would be overkill in this
situation.  You might even get by with an electric fuel pump.  I'd mount
it in the cold side of the system.

